                                <h3>What is Corona Virus (COVID-19)</h3>
                                <p>Coronaviruses are a group of related RNA viruses that cause diseases in mammals and birds. 
                                    In humans and birds, they cause respiratory tract infections that can range from mild to lethal.
                                     Mild illnesses in humans include some cases of the common cold (which is also caused by other
                                      viruses, predominantly rhinoviruses), while more lethal varieties can cause SARS, MERS, and 
                                      COVID-19.</p>
                                      <p>
                                          Coronaviruses are large, roughly spherical particles with unique surface projections.
                                          Their size is highly variable and generally is an average diameter of 120 nm. 
                                          Extreme sizes are known from 50 to 200 nm in diameter. 
                                          The total molecular weight is on average 40,000 kDa. They are enclosed in an envelope embedded with a 
                                          number of protein molecules. The lipid bilayer envelope, membrane proteins,
                                           and nucleocapsid protect the virus when it is outside the host cell.
